{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896732784,"sessionID":"ses_28453c10fffeNT2KVEuElwpEgY","part":{"id":"prt_d7bad03bf001DrsrWpMY0CPJKt","messageID":"msg_d7bacbe48001abv0v3XD3080p6","sessionID":"ses_28453c10fffeNT2KVEuElwpEgY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: MetadataService and Data Models (AR-025)\n\n## AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `MetadataService` class and associated data models (`AgentMetadata`, `MetadataOptions`) to provide a centralized, type-safe mechanism for managing agent metadata throughout the AgentCube CLI lifecycle. This service SHALL serve as the single source of truth for agent configuration, enabling consistent validation, persistence, and retrieval of metadata across all CLI operations.\n\nThe `MetadataService` SHALL:\n- Define a Pydantic-based `AgentMetadata` model with comprehensive field validation\n- Provide CRUD operations for metadata files with fallback loading strategy\n- Validate workspace contents against metadata requirements\n- Support language-specific validation (Python, Java)\n- Enforce schema constraints via Pydantic validators\n- Offer a lightweight `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI overrides\n- Enable seamless integration with all runtime classes\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **AgentMetadata Pydantic Model**\n   - Complete field definitions with types and defaults\n   - Field validators for `language`, `build_mode`, and `port`\n   - Support for 20+ configuration fields\n   - `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` for clean YAML serialization\n\n2. **MetadataOptions Dataclass**\n   - CLI override options for pack command\n   - Factory method `from_options()` for dict-to-dataclass conversion\n   - Default values aligned with `AgentMetadata`\n\n3. **MetadataService Core Implementation**\n   - `load_metadata()` with multi-file fallback (agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml)\n   - `save_metadata()` with consistent YAML formatting\n   - `update_metadata()` for atomic load-modify-save operations\n   - `validate_workspace()` with language-specific checks\n\n4. **Schema Validation**\n   - `validate_language()` → accepts `['python', 'java']` (case-insensitive)\n   - `validate_build_mode()` → accepts `['local', 'cloud']` (case-insensitive)\n   - `validate_port()` → range 1-65535\n   - Pydantic `ValidationError` for schema violations\n\n5. **Workspace Validation**\n   - `_validate_python_workspace()` → requires at least one `*.py` file\n   - `_validate_java_workspace()` → requires `pom.xml`\n   - Extensible for additional languages\n\n6. **YAML Persistence**\n   - `yaml.safe_load()` for secure deserialization\n   - `yaml.dump()` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`\n   - Canonical filename: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n7. **Error Handling**\n   - `FileNotFoundError` for missing metadata files\n   - `ValueError` for workspace validation failures\n   - `ValidationError` for schema violations\n   - Structured logging via `self.logger`\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. **Multiple Metadata Versions**: Migration logic for schema versioning\n2. **Remote Metadata Storage**: Cloud-based metadata persistence\n3. **Encrypted Metadata**: Field-level encryption for sensitive values\n4. **JSON Support**: Only YAML format is supported\n5. **Metadata Templates**: No scaffolding/template generation\n6. **Auto-discovery**: No automatic detection of entrypoints or ports\n7. **IDE Integration**: No LSP or editor-specific features\n8. **GUI Editor**: No graphical metadata editor\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### AgentMetadata Model Structure\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    # Required fields\n    agent_name: str                    # Unique identifier\n    entrypoint: str                    # Launch command\n\n    # Core configuration (with defaults)\n    language: str = \"python\"           # python | java\n    port: int = 8080                   # 1-65535\n    build_mode: str = \"local\"          # local | cloud\n\n    # Optional metadata\n    description: Optional[str]         # Human-readable summary\n    version: Optional[str]             # Semantic version\n    region: Optional[str]              # Deployment region\n\n    # File references\n    requirements_file: str = \"requirements.txt\"\n\n    # Registry configuration\n    registry_url: str = \"\"\n    registry_username: str = \"\"\n    registry_password: str = \"\"\n\n    # AgentCube-specific URLs\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str]\n    router_url: Optional[str]\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str]\n\n    # Health check configuration\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str]\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int]\n\n    # Runtime state\n    agent_id: Optional[str]            # Assigned by AgentCube\n    session_id: Optional[str]          # Current session\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict]     # K8s deployment info\n    image: Optional[Dict]              # Container image info\n    auth: Optional[Dict]               # Authentication config\n\n    # Pack tracking\n    pack_timestamp: Optional[str]\n    dockerfile_generated: Optional[bool]\n```\n\n### MetadataOptions Dataclass Structure\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n```\n\n### MetadataService Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Initialize with optional verbose logging.\"\"\"\n\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    \"\"\"Load with fallback: agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml\"\"\"\n\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Save to agent_metadata.yaml with consistent formatting.\"\"\"\n\n    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    \"\"\"Atomic load-modify-save operation.\"\"\"\n\n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> bool: ...\n    \"\"\"Validate workspace contents against metadata.\"\"\"\n\n    def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Check for *.py files.\"\"\"\n\n    def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Check for pom.xml.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### Metadata Loading Flow\n\n```\nload_metadata(workspace_path)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Try agent_metadata.yaml     │\n│ - Check exists              │\n│ - yaml.safe_load()          │\n│ - AgentMetadata.model_validate()\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Not found\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Try agent.yaml              │\n│ (same process)              │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Not found\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Try metadata.yaml           │\n│ (same process)              │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Not found\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Raise FileNotFoundError     │\n│ \"No metadata file found\"    │\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Metadata Saving Flow\n\n```\nsave_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Prepare Data                │\n│ - model_dump()              │\n│ - exclude_none=True         │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Write YAML                  │\n│ - default_flow_style=False  │\n│ - indent=2                  │\n│ - sort_keys=False           │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Log Success                 │\n│ - \"Saved metadata to {path}\"│\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Workspace Validation Flow\n\n```\nvalidate_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Check Language              │\n│ metadata.language           │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n      ┌───────┴───────┐\n      ▼               ▼\n┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐\n│ \"python\" │    │ \"java\"   │\n└────┬─────┘    └────┬─────┘\n     │               │\n     ▼               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────────┐\n│ _validate_python_       │ │ _validate_java_         │\n│   workspace()           │ │   workspace()           │\n│ - glob(\"*.py\")          │ │ - exists(\"pom.xml\")     │\n│ - Raise if empty        │ │ - Raise if missing      │\n└──────────┬──────────────┘ └──────────┬──────────────┘\n           │                           │\n           └───────────┬───────────────┘\n                       ▼\n              ┌─────────────────┐\n              │ Return True     │\n              │ (or raise)      │\n              └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| Component | Impact | Description |\n|-----------|--------|-------------|\n| `PackRuntime` | High | Uses `MetadataService` for load/save/validate |\n| `BuildRuntime` | High | Uses metadata for build configuration |\n| `PublishRuntime` | High | Uses metadata for deployment parameters |\n| `InvokeRuntime` | High | Uses metadata for endpoint and session |\n| `StatusRuntime` | High | Uses metadata for status lookups |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Medium | Commands depend on metadata structure |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Medium | Defines `MetadataOptions` |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Low | May export `MetadataService` |\n\n### Data Format Changes\n\n**YAML Output Format (agent_metadata.yaml):**\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\ndescription: My agent description\nrequirements_file: requirements.txt\nregistry_url: registry.example.com\nregistry_username: \"\"\nregistry_password: \"\"\nworkload_manager_url: http://workload-manager:8080\nrouter_url: http://router:8080\nreadiness_probe_path: /health\nreadiness_probe_port: 8080\nagent_endpoint: null\nagent_id: null\nsession_id: null\nk8s_deployment: null\nimage: null\nauth: null\npack_timestamp: null\ndockerfile_generated: null\n```\n\n**Loading Precedence:**\n1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (canonical)\n2. `agent.yaml` (fallback 1)\n3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback 2)\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Exception | Message Pattern |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| No metadata file | `FileNotFoundError` | \"No metadata file found in {workspace_path}\" |\n| Invalid YAML | `yaml.YAMLError` | (from yaml.safe_load) |\n| Schema violation | `ValidationError` | Pydantic field errors |\n| Invalid language | `ValidationError` | \"Unsupported language: {v}\" |\n| Invalid build_mode | `ValidationError` | \"Unsupported build_mode: {v}\" |\n| Invalid port | `ValidationError` | \"Invalid port: {v}\" |\n| No Python files | `ValueError` | \"No Python files found in workspace\" |\n| No pom.xml | `ValueError` | \"No pom.xml found in workspace\" |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: JSON instead of YAML\n\n**Approach**: Use JSON as the metadata format.\n\n**Rejected**: YAML is more human-readable and supports comments. YAML is the de facto standard for Kubernetes-related tooling. JSON is more verbose for configuration files.\n\n### Alternative 2: TOML instead of YAML\n\n**Approach**: Use TOML as the metadata format.\n\n**Rejected**: While TOML is good for simple configs, YAML is more familiar in the Kubernetes ecosystem. TOML nesting can become confusing for complex structures like `k8s_deployment`.\n\n### Alternative 3: SQLite/SQL Database\n\n**Approach**: Store metadata in a local SQLite database.\n\n**Rejected**: Overkill for simple configuration. Loses human readability and editability. Makes version control difficult. Adds unnecessary complexity.\n\n### Alternative 4: Dataclasses instead of Pydantic\n\n**Approach**: Use standard Python dataclasses with manual validation.\n\n**Partially Accepted**: `MetadataOptions` uses dataclass (simple, no validation needed). `AgentMetadata` uses Pydantic for robust validation, type coercion, and serialization.\n\n### Alternative 5: Single Metadata File (No Fallback)\n\n**Approach**: Only support `agent_metadata.yaml`, no fallback loading.\n\n**Rejected**: Fallback provides backward compatibility and migration path. Users may have existing `agent.yaml` or `metadata.yaml` files from earlier versions.\n\n### Alternative 6: Auto-generated Entrypoint Detection\n\n**Approach**: Automatically detect entrypoint from Python/Java files.\n\n**Deferred**: Too complex and error-prone. Better to require explicit configuration. Could be added later as an optional feature.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Metadata Loading Verification\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService, AgentMetadata\n\nservice = MetadataService(verbose=True)\n\n# Load from workspace\nmetadata = service.load_metadata(Path(\"/tmp/test-agent\"))\nprint(f\"Loaded: {metadata.agent_name} ({metadata.language})\")\n\n# Access fields\nprint(f\"Entrypoint: {metadata.entrypoint}\")\nprint(f\"Port: {metadata.port}\")\nprint(f\"Build mode: {metadata.build_mode}\")\n```\n\n### Metadata Creation and Saving Verification\n\n```python\n# Create new metadata\nmetadata = AgentMetadata(\n    agent_name=\"my-test-agent\",\n    entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    language=\"python\",\n    port=8080,\n    description=\"Test agent for verification\",\n)\n\n# Save to workspace\nservice.save_metadata(Path(\"/tmp/test-agent\"), metadata)\nprint(\"Saved successfully\")\n```\n\n### Schema Validation Verification\n\n```python\n# Valid metadata\nmetadata = AgentMetadata(\n    agent_name=\"test\",\n    entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    language=\"PYTHON\",  # Case-insensitive\n    port=8080,\n    build_mode=\"LOCAL\",  # Case-insensitive\n)\nprint(f\"Normalized language: {metadata.language}\")  # \"python\"\nprint(f\"Normalized build_mode: {metadata.build_mode}\")  # \"local\"\n\n# Invalid language (will raise ValidationError)\ntry:\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n        language=\"ruby\",\n    )\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n\n# Invalid port (will raise ValidationError)\ntry:\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n        port=99999,\n    )\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n```\n\n### Workspace Validation Verification\n\n```python\n# Python workspace validation\nmetadata = AgentMetadata(\n    agent_name=\"python-agent\",\n    entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    language=\"python\",\n)\n\n# Valid Python workspace (has .py files)\nresult = service.validate_workspace(Path(\"/tmp/python-agent\"), metadata)\nprint(f\"Validation passed: {result}\")\n\n# Invalid Python workspace (no .py files)\ntry:\n    result = service.validate_workspace(Path(\"/tmp/empty-dir\"), metadata)\nexcept ValueError as e:\n    print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n\n# Java workspace validation\nmetadata = AgentMetadata(\n    agent_name=\"java-agent\",\n    entrypoint=\"java -jar app.jar\",\n    language=\"java\",\n)\n\n# Valid Java workspace (has pom.xml)\nresult = service.validate_workspace(Path(\"/tmp/java-agent\"), metadata)\nprint(f\"Validation passed: {result}\")\n```\n\n### MetadataOptions Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n\n# Create from CLI options\noptions = {\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"language\": \"python\",\n    \"port\": 9000,\n}\nmetadata_options = MetadataOptions.from_options(options)\nprint(f\"Agent: {metadata_options.agent_name}\")\nprint(f\"Port: {metadata_options.port}\")\n\n# None values are filtered\noptions_with_none = {\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"description\": None,\n    \"port\": 8080,\n}\nmetadata_options = MetadataOptions.from_options(options_with_none)\nprint(f\"Has description attr: {hasattr(metadata_options, 'description')}\")\n```\n\n### Update Metadata Verification\n\n```python\n# Atomic update\nupdates = {\n    \"version\": \"v1.0.0\",\n    \"description\": \"Updated description\",\n    \"pack_timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n}\n\nupdated = service.update_metadata(Path(\"/tmp/test-agent\"), updates)\nprint(f\"Version: {updated.version}\")\nprint(f\"Description: {updated.description}\")\n```\n\n### Error Handling Verification\n\n```python\n# Missing metadata file\ntry:\n    service.load_metadata(Path(\"/tmp/nonexistent\"))\nexcept FileNotFoundError as e:\n    print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n\n# Invalid YAML\ntry:\n    # Assume /tmp/bad-yaml/agent_metadata.yaml contains invalid YAML\n    service.load_metadata(Path(\"/tmp/bad-yaml\"))\nexcept yaml.YAMLError as e:\n    print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) — CLI package layout and service architecture\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) — Metadata requirements specification\n- [Pydantic Documentation](https://docs.pydantic.dev/) — Pydantic v2 model documentation\n- [PyYAML Documentation](https://pyyaml.org/wiki/PyYAMLDocumentation) — YAML parsing library\n- AR-020 — CLI Pack Command (uses MetadataService for metadata operations)\n- AR-021 — CLI Build Command (uses metadata for build config)\n- AR-022 — CLI Publish Command (uses metadata for deployment)\n- AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Commands (uses metadata for endpoint/session)\n- AR-024 — DockerService Encapsulation — Predecessor using service pattern\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model is defined in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n2. ✅ Model has 20+ fields with proper types and defaults\n3. ✅ `validate_language()` accepts 'python' and 'java' (case-insensitive)\n4. ✅ `validate_build_mode()` accepts 'local' and 'cloud' (case-insensitive)\n5. ✅ `validate_port()` enforces range 1-65535\n6. ✅ `MetadataService` class is implemented\n7. ✅ `load_metadata()` tries agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml\n8. ✅ `save_metadata()` writes to agent_metadata.yaml with consistent formatting\n9. ✅ `update_metadata()` performs atomic load-modify-save\n10. ✅ `validate_workspace()` returns True on success\n11. ✅ `_validate_python_workspace()` raises if no *.py files\n12. ✅ `_validate_java_workspace()` raises if no pom.xml\n13. ✅ YAML uses `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`\n14. ✅ `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` excludes None values\n15. ✅ `MetadataOptions` dataclass is defined in `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n16. ✅ `MetadataOptions.from_options()` filters None values\n17. ✅ Missing metadata file raises `FileNotFoundError`\n18. ✅ Schema violations raise Pydantic `ValidationError`\n19. ✅ All methods use structured logging via `self.logger`\n20. ✅ Verbose mode enables DEBUG level logging\n21. ✅ `MetadataService` is importable from `agentcube.services`\n22. ✅ `AgentMetadata` is importable from `agentcube.services.metadata_service`\n23. ✅ `MetadataOptions` is importable from `agentcube.models.pack_models`\n\n---\n\n*AR-025 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/models/pack_models.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775896732664,"end":1775896732781}}}}
